Class DefaultRecoveryBlock

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.mesos.scheduler.DefaultObservable

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Observable, Block, Element

    public class DefaultRecoveryBlock
extends DefaultBlock
    DefaultRecoveryBlock is an extension of DefaultBlock meant for use with DefaultRecoveryPlanManager. It is responsible for following: 1. Encapsulating RecoveryRequirement 2. Updating launchHappened event.

      • updateOfferStatus

        public void updateOfferStatus(java.util.Collection<Protos.Offer.Operation> operations)
        Description copied from interface: Block
        Notifies the Block whether the OfferRequirement previously returned by Block.start() has been successfully accepted/fulfilled. The operations param is empty when no offers matching the requirement previously returned by #clone() could be found. This is only called if {@link #start()} returned a non-{@code null} {@link OfferRequirement}.
